pull_request.title: Feature/manage blog
pull_request.body:
#7 

This pull request introduces several significant improvements and refactors to the blog API and its frontend integration. The main changes include replacing HTML content with Markdown, expanding backend CRUD operations for blogs, updating API endpoints and DTOs, and wiring up new frontend API functions and routes to support these enhancements.

**Backend: Blog Model, Repository, and API Enhancements**

* Replaced the `HtmlContent` property in the `Blog` entity with `MarkdownContent`, updated the corresponding database schema, and provided migration scripts to handle the change. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-2481eebda334aebff955225460e5d9763ad74daf694519ec36c3b387fc5422e6L8-R8) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-8d7b064066f74b533e2eec68fa155cdced33730f21e1987a0db8e36b28c4c0b9R1-R28) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-dc42b490d610293168bc4878cbb6403f677b2745d7cf5f65a6646eb961668f41R1-R95) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-3fa3c4e187c30fa7d264bc14a402407eeab03285b9048eee0737e95a7ce0c835L41-R41)
* Extended the `IBlogRepository` interface and its implementation to include async CRUD operations: `CreateAsync`, `GetByIdAsync`, `GetByUserIdAsync`, `DeleteByIdAsync`, and `UpdateAsync`. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-379123606f202f19ee40c62163447a8aeaacea6b3e88e43159b5891a4a47df5cL5-R10) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-97a44e41dfe3bc06c48a49fa6bf67275714162a6703b32d6d3219c8c4bdb4d30L9-R78)
* Updated the `BlogController` API to support creating, updating, deleting, and filtering blogs by user, and switched to using DTOs for input. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-905003fc5438ddc9d292634c46fe0d969a8794a5d0d137c8ef214cb0cecf92e2R2-R8) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-905003fc5438ddc9d292634c46fe0d969a8794a5d0d137c8ef214cb0cecf92e2L18-R84) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-a37b67a3fb72f443e110abb9c70e1b9bc7f84e18e8ad5953480931ecb0e81ffbR1-R9) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-8052c623d6af8fba0c29d9aca1b6578ddfd5bcfeac2b01a700d663d741972607R1-R8)

**Frontend: API Integration and Routing**

* Added new API functions for creating, updating, deleting, and fetching blogs (all, by user, by id) in the frontend, and updated the `Blog` model to use `markdownContent`. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-80c5388db68451ff7864efb8515789bb877c8262713cb9234e8bac8b865fa750R1-R7) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-33171951d4906a62def0752c132bebabe636e2bc660fa98a1fc1b5466ec82c5cR1-R8) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-8bcc66239dc602e0c2a40f56a8c28e0e6b1996c635e44d96ba5b2c166fb34030R1-R7) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-d81a9eec1d489697dd047af91e513f3fb13e484dad7044b9fdf3f340e7790a1fR1-R7) [[5]](diffhunk://#diff-6e8dd19358ccb75012441d9a6ff5bdbf4e43373a62ec60f3dcd61a5bedff0cfdR1-R8) [[6]](diffhunk://#diff-8092eff290e28bac0377e9a9c9d6ec9edc605142eba3f1cf6a9600513e23c79fR1-R8) [[7]](diffhunk://#diff-dc410f057ee5884f7f781e092615778f4b9016ab40fac1be59be530dd53f55a5L2-R8)
* Introduced new protected routes for blog editing and creation in the frontend routing configuration. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-233731a3dcb2263ceb18f166a709aab8bc704a40df2e78fc40bed15eda1b5237R6-R7) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-233731a3dcb2263ceb18f166a709aab8bc704a40df2e78fc40bed15eda1b5237R21-R22)

**Frontend: Dependency Updates**

* Added `react-markdown` and `@tailwindcss/typography` to support Markdown rendering and improved styling. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-195ca64bb016f9c1c67e94c3b8c4ed49e8602655e199536362764709056d6b1fR18-R25) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-195ca64bb016f9c1c67e94c3b8c4ed49e8602655e199536362764709056d6b1fL33)

These changes collectively modernize the blog content format, provide full CRUD support, and ensure the frontend is aligned with the updated backend API.

issue.title: 我尝试适配1080p分辨率

labels.name: wontfix / 不做
labels.description: This will not be worked on

issue.body:
### 你的功能请求是否与问题有关？

因为之前ALAS不适配1080p的主要原因是截图速度问题，如今mumu12的nemu_ipc截图方案速度已经很快，我在想现在是否能在1080p下使用脚本。

因为有时看剧情和皮肤或是大建等情况确实需要浏览，720p真有点糊不太够用，而模拟器需要重启才能切换分辨率，十分不方便，这个需求对碧蓝航线我感觉挺大的，尤其是现在优化过UI后。

我在尝试增加可选分辨率后，在1080p下日志只能显示"Unknown ui page"，截图正常，我浏览文档和源码后发现匹配图片貌似是根据720p下的实际X,Y轴位置，所以无法匹配？

### 解决方案

所以要支持1080p是需要修改所有图片及位置吗？还是说可以乘比例放大坐标直接匹配720p的图片，是否会导致准确率问题？真心希望能增加对mumu12的nemu_ipc截图方案1080p的支持。

### 其他内容

_No response_

issue.title: Re-enable code coverage report in Python 3.12

labels.name: github_actions
labels.description: Pull requests that update GitHub Actions code

issue.body:
### Details about the quacc environment

- **quacc version**: 0.4.5
- **Python version**: 3.12.1


### What is the issue?

For some reason, the Python 3.12 GitHub actions runner is extremely slow when coverage reports are generated. This is not observed in Python 3.9, 3.10, or 3.11.

For now, I have removed coverage report generation in the GitHub Actions test suite for Python 3.12 until the issue is resolved.

issue.title: `fmt.Printf("%v", map[any]int{nil: 1, 1: 1})` causes GnoVM panic
issue.body:
**Description:**
When attempting to print a map containing `nil` as a key alongside another value, GnoVM crashes with a nil pointer dereference.

**Reproduction:**

```go
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
	mp := map[any]int{nil: 1, 1: 1}
	fmt.Printf("%v", mp)
}
```

**Expected behavior:**
The map should be printed correctly, e.g.:

map[nil:1 1:1]

DASHBOARD PRIVACY IMPROVEMENTS:
- Remove all secret information from player status cards
- Hide player stockpiles, credits, protected resources
- Remove colony stockpiles table (was showing strategic data)
- Add visual progress bar for game readiness
- Only show: player names, tribes, submission status
- Maintain strategic gameplay by hiding opponent resources

RESULT: Game now properly balanced with unique PINs per player
and no strategic information leakage in dashboard.

issue.title: How do I disable Visual Editing (and react deps)?
issue.body:
<!--

 **IMPORTANT!**
Please make sure to look for an answer to your question in our documentation before asking a question here.

If you have a general question regarding {{ name }} use Discord `modules` channel. Thanks!

Documentation: {{ docs }}
Nuxt Discord: https://discord.nuxtjs.org/

-->
I'm not using Visual Editing, but still have problems like #1277 and #1284 which breaks HMR. Looks like this feature has some react dependencies which not always work well. So would it be possible to ditch it?

I should note that it only happens if I install deps with `bun`.

The current workaround (nuxt.config.ts):
```
  vite: {
    optimizeDeps: {
      include: ['react-compiler-runtime', 'react', 'react-dom']
    },
  },
```

This workaround makes builds and dev compiling at least 5 times longer.

comment.body:
This appears to be the only current workaround for
 ```
Uncaught (in promise) SyntaxError: The requested module '/_nuxt/@fs/C:/wamp64/www/temp/nuxt-sanity-demo/node_modules/react-compiler-runtime/dist/index.js?v=f8fd7759' does not provide an export named 'c'
``` 
and
 ```
Uncaught (in promise) SyntaxError: The requested module '/_nuxt/@fs/C:/wamp64/www/temp/nuxt-sanity-demo/node_modules/react/index.js?v=8bc1c419' does not provide an export named 'useSyncExternalStore'
``` 
errors mentioned in other tickets, but this is not a viable solution IMO - for one it requires users to search Github issues before they can get Nuxt to compile a single page.

is this something controllable by the package author, or is it an issue in `react-compiler-runtime`?
